            <opener>  
                <handShift rend="printed"/>
                <dateline>
                <name type="place">EDITORIAL &#183; DEPARTMENT</name>
                <name type="place">THE CENTURY &#183; MAGAZINE</name>
                <name type="place">UNION &#183; SQUARE &#183; NEW &#183; YORK<lb/></name>
                <handShift rend="manuscript"/>
                <name type="place">Marion, Mass,</name>
                    <date when="1887-07-01">1st July 1887.</date>
                </dateline>
                <salute>My dear Whitman,</salute>
            </opener>
            <p> I am delighted that you liked Miss Phelps's story<ptr target="n4306"/> so well. We sent your card on to
                her&#8212;knowing she would prize it. The story has made a profound impression.</p>
            <closer>
                <salute>Sincerely</salute>
                <signed>R.W. Gilder</signed>
            </closer>
            <postscript>
                <p>I wish we could put you in front of our big chimney.
                </p>
            </postscript>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="hsp.00006.002_large.jpg" type="verso"/>
